Italy Needs Swift Budget Approval, Eni’s Recchi Tells La Stampa

-- B y   L o r e n z o   T o t a r o
-- 
2011-08-22T06:47:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-22/italy-needs-swift-budget-approval-eni-s-recchi-tells-la-stampa.html
Italian lawmakers need to swiftly
approve the budget cuts passed this month by the government in
order to restore investor confidence,  Eni SpA (ENI) ’s Chairman
Giuseppe Recchi told Il Sole 24 Ore in an interview.  “The best thing is that the Parliament passes it as it
is,” Sole cited Recchi as saying. “The leadership of the
country has to be recreated so that decisions taken can be
implemented immediately and become final.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lorenzo Totaro in Rome at 
 ltotaro@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Craig Stirling at 
 cstirling1@bloomberg.net  